      "message": "Curious about the need for this. Is the plan to use the unique key to store/find things in the free pool?\n\nJust checking my understanding: We will need a way to get back to resources that have been used once or more already because scratch lookups won\u0027t work since the resource is already ref\u0027ed in another proxy. Which I assume also means that resources assigned to a proxy by the allocator are not in pending-IO state.\n\nCould we just use the ptr to the resource? Either by taking a ref in the free pool or by claiming that another proxy must already be holding the surface since it is in the free pool?",
